18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Economic Development
21 SUBTITLE 12. PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY.
22 12–1201.
23 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
24 INDICATED.
25 (B) “AUTHORITY” MEANS THE SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY.
26 (C) “BOARD” MEANS THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THE AUTHORITY.
27 (D) “BUFFER ZONE” MEANS THE AREA WITHIN 250 YARDS OF THE TARGET
28 AREA.
29 (E) “TARGET AREA” MEANS THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD
30 INTERSECTION CORRIDOR IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
31 12–1202.

HOUSE BILL 1452 3
1 THIS SUBTITLE SHALL BE LIBERALLY CONSTRUED TO ACCOMPLISH ITS
2 PURPOSES.
3 12–1203.
4 (A) THERE IS A SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY IN PRINCE
5 GEORGE’S COUNTY.
6 (B) THE AUTHORITY IS A BODY POLITIC AND CORPORATE AND IS AN
7 INSTRUMENTALITY OF THE STATE.
8 (C) THE EXERCISE BY THE AUTHORITY OF A POWER UNDER THIS SUBTITLE
9 IS THE PERFORMANCE OF AN ESSENTIAL GOVERNMENTAL FUNCTION.
10 (D) THE GOVERNOR MAY SHALL INCLUDE EACH YEAR IN THE STATE
11 ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF $500,000 TO THE AUTHORITY IN
12 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
13 (E) BEGINNING FISCAL YEAR 2036, THE AUTHORITY SHALL BE
14 SELF–SUSTAINING.
15 12–1204.
16 (A) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY FINDS THAT:
17 (1) THERE EXISTS WITHIN VARIOUS NEIGHBORHOODS IN PRINCE
18 GEORGE’S COUNTY, PARTICULARLY THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD
19 INTERSECTION CORRIDOR, A NEED FOR RESIDENTIAL AND COMMERCIAL
20 DEVELOPMENT OR REDEVELOPMENT IN FURTHERANCE OF THE PUBLIC’S INTEREST;
21 (2) THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD INTERSECTION
22 CORRIDOR HAS EXPERIENCED LOW HOUSING AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT IN THE
23 COMMUNITY FOR DECADES;
24 (3) AREAS IN THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD
25 INTERSECTION CORRIDOR INCLUDE BOTH AREAS THAT ARE CONSIDERED SLUM OR
26 BLIGHTED AND AREAS THAT ARE DETERIORATED OR SUBJECT TO FURTHER
27 DETERIORATING CONDITION, AND THOSE AREAS ARE IN NEED OF DEVELOPMENT OR
28 REDEVELOPMENT FOR THE PUBLIC BENEFIT;
29 (4) THE REVITALIZATION OF AREAS WITHIN THE SUITLAND ROAD
30 AND SILVER HILL ROAD INTERSECTION CORRIDOR NEEDING COMMERCIAL
31 DEVELOPMENT OR REDEVELOPMENT IS AN ESSENTIAL GOVERNMENTAL FUNCTION

4 HOUSE BILL 1452
1 AND IS A PUBLIC USE THAT WILL CONFER A PUBLIC BENEFIT ON CITIZENS OF
2 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY BY:
3 (I) RELIEVING CONDITIONS OF UNEMPLOYMENT;
4 (II) ENCOURAGING THE INCREASE OF COMMERCE AND A
5 BALANCED ECONOMY;
6 (III) ASSISTING IN THE RETENTION OF BUSINESSES AND
7 RESIDENTS;
8 (IV) ATTRACTING NEW INDUSTRIES AND COMMERCE;
9 (V) PROMOTING ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AND GROWTH; AND
10 (VI) GENERALLY PROMOTING THE HEALTH, WELFARE, AND
11 PUBLIC SAFETY OF RESIDENTS IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY AND INCREASING
12 PROPERTY TAX REVENUES FOR THE STATE AND PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
13 (5) THE ESTABLISHMENT OF THIS PUBLIC AUTHORITY TO PROVIDE
14 FINANCIAL RESOURCES FOR THE DEVELOPMENT AND ESTABLISHMENT OF
15 RESIDENCES AND BUSINESSES THROUGH COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS IN THE
16 TARGET AREA WILL SIGNIFICANTLY IMPROVE PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY
17 NEIGHBORHOODS AND INCREASE PROPERTY TAX REVENUES FOR THE STATE AND
18 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
19 (6) THE AUTHORITY IS THE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY
20 FOR THE STATE TO BENEFIT THE NEIGHBORHOODS OF PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY
21 WITHIN THE TARGET AREA.
22 (B) THE LEGISLATIVE PURPOSES OF THE AUTHORITY ARE TO:
23 (1) REVIVE THE VARIOUS COMMUNITIES ALONG THE SUITLAND ROAD
24 AND SILVER HILL ROAD INTERSECTION CORRIDOR IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
25 (2) PROMOTE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT;
26 (3) ENCOURAGE THE INCREASE OF BUSINESS ACTIVITY, COMMERCE,
27 AND A BALANCED ECONOMY IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
28 (4) HELP TO RETAIN AND ATTRACT BUSINESS ACTIVITY AND
29 COMMERCE IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND

HOUSE BILL 1452 5
1 (5) PROMOTE THE HEALTH, PUBLIC SAFETY, RIGHT OF GAINFUL
2 EMPLOYMENT, AND WELFARE OF RESIDENTS OF PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
3 (C) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY INTENDS THAT:
4 (1) THE AUTHORITY OPERATE AND EXERCISE ITS CORPORATE
5 POWERS ALONG THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD INTERSECTION
6 CORRIDOR IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
7 (2) WITHOUT LIMITING ITS AUTHORITY TO OTHERWISE EXERCISE ITS
8 POWERS, THE AUTHORITY EXERCISES ITS POWERS TO ASSIST PRIVATE REAL ESTATE
9 ENTITIES AND NONPROFIT COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT CORPORATIONS TO
10 DEVELOP AND REHABILITATE HOUSING AND COMMERCIAL UNITS IN PRINCE
11 GEORGE’S COUNTY AND SUPPORT LOCAL ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AGENCIES TO
12 CONTRIBUTE TO THE EXPANSION, MODERNIZATION, AND RETENTION OF EXISTING
13 ENTERPRISES IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY AS WELL AS THE ATTRACTION OF NEW
14 BUSINESSES TO PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
15 (3) THE AUTHORITY SHOULD NOT OWN AND OPERATE A PROJECT
16 UNLESS:
17 (I) THE BOARD DETERMINES BY RESOLUTION THAT THE
18 PRIVATE SECTOR HAS NOT DEMONSTRATED SERIOUS AND SIGNIFICANT INTEREST
19 AND DEVELOPMENT CAPACITY TO OWN AND OPERATE THE PROJECT; OR
20 (II) A REPRESENTATIVE OF A GOVERNMENTAL UNIT REQUESTS
21 IN WRITING THAT THE AUTHORITY OWN AND OPERATE THE PROJECT.
22 12–1205.
23 (A) (1) EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE PROVIDED IN THIS SECTION, IN
24 EXERCISING ITS POWERS, THE AUTHORITY:
25 (I) MAY CARRY OUT THE PURPOSES OF THE AUTHORITY
26 WITHOUT THE CONSENT OF ANY STATE UNIT; AND
27 (II) IS NOT SUBJECT TO:
28 1. SUBTITLES 1 THROUGH 3 OF THIS TITLE; OR
