6 (A) THE AUTHORITY SHALL:
7 (1) SUPPORT THE DEVELOPMENT AND APPROVAL OF A
8 COMPREHENSIVE NEIGHBORHOOD REVITALIZATION PLAN IN THE TARGET AREA
9 AND THE BUFFER ZONE TO BENEFIT:
10 (I) THE RESIDENTS;
11 (II) HOUSING;
12 (III) NEIGHBORHOODS;
13 (IV) ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT; AND
14 (V) TRANSPORTATION, INCLUDING MOTOR VEHICLES AND
15 PEDESTRIANS; AND
16 (2) WORK IN COORDINATION WITH THE RESIDENTS OF THE TARGET
17 AREA AND THE BUFFER ZONE TO DEVELOP A COMPREHENSIVE NEIGHBORHOOD
18 REVITALIZATION PLAN.
19 (B) THE AUTHORITY MAY, BY A MAJORITY VOTE OF ALL MEMBERS OF THE
20 AUTHORITY, MODIFY THE BOUNDARIES OF THE TARGET AREA AND THE BUFFER
21 ZONE.
22 (C) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 15, 2027, THE AUTHORITY SHALL REPORT
23 ITS COMPREHENSIVE NEIGHBORHOOD REVITALIZATION STRATEGY, INCLUDING ANY
24 PROCUREMENT ACTIVITIES UNDERTAKEN BY THE AUTHORITY, TO THE GOVERNOR
